INSERT INTO `main_content` VALUES (228, 7, 20, 0, 'Request Information', 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, '2003-11-24', '2007-11-15', '2004-05-31', '16', '7', '', '2003-11-24', '2003-12-01', 0, 100, '<P><FONT size=3><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">If you are interested in receiving information about </SPAN><?xml:namespace prefix = st1 /><st1:place><st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Peoria</SPAN></st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"> </SPAN><st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Christian</SPAN></st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"> </SPAN><st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">School</SPAN></st1:PlaceName></st1:place><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman"> along with an Admissions packet, please call&nbsp;us at (309)686-4500 or fill out the following online form. We will mail the information to you.</SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>', 41, -3, 0);
INSERT INTO `main_content` VALUES (329, 5, 10, 0, 'First Grade', 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, '2004-02-19', '2014-05-31', '2014-05-31', '2', '18', '', '2004-02-19', '2004-08-12', 1, 100, '<P></P><FONT size=2>\r\n<P>Our first grade provides a strong academic foundation in phonics-based Reading, English, Spelling, Mathematics, Science, Social Studies, and Health. The Bible is integrated into all curriculum areas as well as being a course of study by itself. Students also participate in Accelerated Reader, chapel, library, music, and physical education. Other activities include Grandparents Day, Science Fair, Speech Meet, and music concerts. Three grade-level field trips are also taken: Wildlife Prairie Park, Forest Park Nature Center, and the Civic Center Youth Theatre.</P>\r\n<P></P></FONT>', 0, -3, 0);
INSERT INTO `main_content` VALUES (330, 5, 20, 0, 'Second Grade', 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, '2004-02-19', '2014-05-31', '2014-05-31', '2', '2', '', '2004-02-19', '2004-02-19', 1, 100, '<P></P><FONT size=2>\r\n<P>Second grade is a year of growth. We encourage each child to reach his/her potential. Our reading program is a phonics-based approach. Oral reading is an important part of second grade. In writing we help each child to write complete sentences and to build a strong paragraph. In mathematics, our year begins with a review of the basic addition/subtraction facts, then on to money and time. We also introduce 2; 3-and 4-digit addition and subtraction, and we introduce up through the 5s in multiplication. We realize each student has different learning styles; therefore, our teaching is enhanced with various games and other hands-on activities. There are two field trips planned for second graders. In the fall we visit a local apple orchard, and in the spring we go to Bicycle Safety Town where the students review safety rules and then ride bikes on scaled down roads. Another highlight of second grade is Colonial Day. Colonial Day is a time for the students to step back in time and learn how the colonists lived. Some activities include: dipping candles, dying cloth, making butter and playing colonial games.</P>\r\n<P></P></FONT>', 0, -3, 0);
INSERT INTO `main_content` VALUES (331, 5, 30, 0, 'Third Grade', 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, '2004-02-19', '2014-05-31', '2014-05-31', '2', '2', '', '2004-02-19', '2004-02-19', 1, 100, '<P></P><FONT size=2>\r\n<P>Welcome to third grade at PCS! Third grade at Peoria Christian School is an exciting year of learning and fun! Our Christ-centered curriculum leads students into a world of change as they begin to develop more responsibility as well as independent study skills. Our year in third grade includes daily devotions and prayer, special programs and service projects, and two annual field trips to Wildlife Prairie Park and the Peoria Civic Center for a production of Charles Dickens "A Christmas Carol." In third grade we focus on multiplication mastery. We enjoy creative writing, book reports and a science notebook project on vertebrates. Third grade at Peoria Christian promises to be a year of growth, not only as students, but also as godly young men and women.</P>\r\n<P></P></FONT>', 0, -3, 0);
INSERT INTO `main_content` VALUES (332, 5, 40, 0, 'Fourth Grade', 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, '2004-02-19', '2014-05-31', '2014-05-31', '2', '2', '', '2004-02-19', '2004-02-19', 1, 100, '<P></P><FONT size=2>\r\n<P>Fourth grade is an exciting year filled with lots of academic and spiritual growth. Students expand on skills mastered previously as well as meet new challenges with fun and excitement.</P>\r\n<P></P>\r\n<P>Fourth grade is a year of transition. We are partially self-contained and partially departmentalized. Each teacher teaches a subject in their field of expertise, in addition to the core subjects of reading, math, spelling, and Bible. Highlights include field trips to places which include Funks Prairie Home, a trip on the Spirit of Peoria and Forest Park Nature Center, service projects such as helping out the Womens Pregnancy Center and Christmas Caroling at Retirement Homes, the Patriotic Program, Science Fair, Spelling Bee, Speech Meet and Math Olympics.</P>\r\n<P></P>\r\n<P>Our curriculum includes a language program which has an emphasis on writing and grammar, hands-on science classes, and math which takes the students to a level that prepares them for more advanced classes.</P>\r\n<P></P></FONT>', 0, -3, 0);
