assignments will be posted by </SPAN><?xml:namespace prefix = st1 /><st1:time Minute="0" Hour="13"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial">1:00 p.m.</SPAN></st1:time><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> every school day.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>In addition to the website, homework will also be available by calling the </SPAN><st1:State><st1:place><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial">California</SPAN></st1:place></st1:State><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> campus.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN><?xml:namespace prefix = o /><o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><o:p><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>The on-line Homework Hotline allows us to provide more information and details than we can do over the phone.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Not only will we give you the daily homework assignments, we will also include the work that was done in the classroom, upcoming quizzes and tests, and future assignments.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><o:p><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>So whether you were out-of-school or simply forgot what your assignments were for today, you can find out by checking out the Homework Hotline page for your grade.</FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3><A href="../public_pdf/homework5.pdf" target=_blank>Homework Hotline for 5th Grade</A></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3><A href="../public_pdf/homework6.pdf" target=_blank>Homework Hotline for 6th Grade</A></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3><A href="../public_pdf/homework7.pdf" target=_blank>Homework Hotline for 7th Grade</A></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3><A href="../public_pdf/homework8.pdf" target=_blank>Homework Hotline for 8th Grade</A></FONT></SPAN></P>', 1, -3, 37);
INSERT INTO `main_content` VALUES (246, 10, 10, 0, 'Little girl praying', 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, '2003-12-04', '2004-08-30', '2004-08-30', '6', '6', '', '2003-12-04', '2004-08-03', 0, 100, '<P>\r\n<P><SPAN class=body><B><IMG style="WIDTH: 195px; HEIGHT: 252px" height=1636 alt="" hspace=2 src="http://www.peoriachristian.org/uploads/jkammerer_0_Little Girl Praying_1070565733_100_0385.JPG" width=758 align=right vspace=2 border=5>THE ANNUAL FUND - $200,000<BR></B></SPAN><BR>\r\n<TABLE cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=2 border=0>\r\n<TBODY>\r\n<TR>\r\n<TD vAlign=top align=right width=20><IMG height=8 src="http://www.wcastl.org/images/bullet2.gif" width=8 vspace=4 border=0></TD>\r\n<TD vAlign=top align=left width=422>\r\n<P><SPAN class=body>During the 2003-2004 school year, the cost of educating our students is $300,000 more than we will receive from net tuition and other income. In addition, $20,000 is needed for necessary additions and improvements (eg. technology resources, new van).</SPAN></P></TD></TR>\r\n<TR>\r\n<TD vAlign=top align=right width=20><IMG height=8 src="http://www.wcastl.org/images/bullet2.gif" width=8 vspace=4 border=0></TD>\r\n<TD vAlign=top align=left width=422>\r\n<P><SPAN class=body>Therefore our total Annual Fund goal is $320,000, just over $334 per student.&nbsp;PCS depends on raising the Annual Fund by June 30th, 2004.</SPAN></P></TD></TR>\r\n<TR>\r\n<TD vAlign=top align=right width=20><IMG height=8 src="http://www.wcastl.org/images/bullet2.gif" width=8 vspace=4 border=0></TD>\r\n<TD vAlign=top align=left width=422>\r\n<P><SPAN class=body>Traditionally, Annual Fund gifts are unrestricted from $5 to $50,000 in the form of cash or stocks. Gifts are made by alumni, churches, current parents, parents of alumni, grandparents, and friends of the school. </SPAN></P></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><BR><BR><SPAN class=body><B>WHAT WILL YOUR GIFT BE?<BR><BR></B></SPAN>\r\n<TABLE cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=2 border=0>\r\n<TBODY>\r\n<TR>\r\n<TD vAlign=top align=right width=20><IMG height=8 src="http://www.wcastl.org/images/bullet2.gif" width=8 vspace=4 border=0></TD>\r\n<TD vAlign=top align=left width=279>\r\n<P><SPAN class=body>Our $334 goal per student is a guideline. Some can\'t afford it and some can give more. Please give in accordance with how God has blessed you.</SPAN></P></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></P>', 0, -1, 0);
INSERT INTO `main_content` VALUES (249, 10, 40, 0, 'Material Needs', 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, '2003-12-04', '2004-05-31', '2004-05-31', '6', '6', '', '2003-12-04', '2003-12-04', 0, 100, '<P>\r\n<P>Peoria Christian School is thankful for the generous gifts that have been given over the years.&nbsp; Many of the&nbsp;items listed&nbsp;below are essential for the daily productive operation of the school. Please review the list and if you feel compelled to contribute contact the Advancement Department at 309-686-4500 Ext: 33 or email <A href="mailto:jkammerer@peoriachristian.org">jkammerer@peoriachristian.org</A>. </P>\r\n<P align=center><STRONG><U>Office and Schools</U></STRONG></P>\r\n<P align=center>Color Lazer Printer</P>\r\n<P align=center>Copy Machine</P>\r\n<P align=center>15 Passenger Bus</P>\r\n<P align=center>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P align=center><STRONG><U>Maintenance &amp; Grounds</U></STRONG>&nbsp;</P>\r\n<P align=center>Hammer Drill-portable cordless</P>\r\n<P align=center>1/2 Drill 9 amp</P>\r\n<P align=center>Power Miter Box</P>\r\n<P align=center>Snow Thrower</P>\r\n<P align=center>&nbsp;</P>', 0, -3, 0);
INSERT INTO `main_content` VALUES (250, 10, 30, 0, 'Annual Banquet', 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, '2003-12-04', '2004-05-31', '2004-05-31', '6', '6', '', '2003-12-04', '2003-12-04', 0, 100, '<P></P><FONT face=Georgia>\r\n<P>Our 53rd Annual Banquet was a tremendous success. The Lord was present that night and I hope you enjoyed Tyler Griggs, Natalie Debelak, and Skip Dampiers testimonies. They were compelling to listen to and encouraging to see how God had worked in their lives through PCS. Tony Evans and Anthony Evans Jr. were incredible. Dr. Evans laid the foundation and principles why Christian education is so needed in todays world. Anthonys performance was spiritually uplifting and we will let you know when his CD is out on the market.</P></FONT><FONT face=Georgia size=1></FONT><FONT face=Georgia>\r\n<P>Our goal for the night was $125,000.00 and God blessed us with $108,550.00. Praise God! That was a great start for the year but we need to press-on toward meeting this years goals. If you were at the banquet you may have noticed the pictures of the students on the tables. Those students represent one of the reasons we are here. The gap between tuition and our operating cost is $376.00 per student. That difference totals $368,480.00. God has blessed PCS in years past and my prayer for the school is, Now unto him that is able to do exceeding abundantly above all that we ask or think, according to the power that worketh in us</FONT><FONT face=Georgia size=2>, </FONT><FONT face=Georgia>Eph 3:20</FONT><FONT face=Georgia size=2>.</FONT><FONT face=Georgia> If you were unable to attend the banquet and would like to assist us in our financial goal please contact Joe Kammerer in the Advancement Department, 309-686-4500 Ext: 33 or email <A href="mailto:jkammerer@peoriachristian.org">jkammerer@peoriachristian.org</A>.</P></FONT><FONT face=Georgia size=1></FONT><FONT face=Georgia>\r\n<P>I want to thank all who helped out with this years banquet. Ruth Hauer was our chairperson and she did a wonderful job. PCS wants to acknowledge the businesses and individuals that sponsored bringing Dr. Evans and Anthony to the banquet; they were Dave and Dan Maloof, Entec Services, Signs Now, and John Myatt Insurance &amp; Financial Services. Again, I hope you enjoyed the evening and were blessed at the banquet. </P></FONT>', 0, 2, 0);
INSERT INTO `main_content` VALUES (251, 10, 30, 0, 'Golf Classic', 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, '2003-12-04', '2004-05-31', '2004-05-31', '6', '6', '', '2003-12-04', '2003-12-04', 1, 100, '<P></P><B><I>\r\n<P align=center><IMG style="WIDTH: 211px; HEIGHT: 177px" height=1333 alt="" hspace=2 src="http://www.peoriachristian.org/uploads/jkammerer_2_Team on the green_1070570577_100_0794.JPG" width=1074 align=left vspace=2 border=5><IMG style="WIDTH: 227px; HEIGHT: 176px" height=1291 alt="" hspace=2 src="http://www.peoriachristian.org/uploads/jkammerer_0_Broken Club_1070570577_100_0791.JPG" width=798 align=right vspace=2 border=5><IMG style="WIDTH: 188px; HEIGHT: 174px" height=1391 alt="" hspace=2 src="http://www.peoriachristian.org/uploads/jkammerer_1_PCS Golf Team_1070570577_100_0773.JPG" width=1100 align=bottom vspace=2 border=5></P>\r\n<P align=center>Thank you for making 7th Annual Fall Classic a Success.</P>\r\n<P align=center></P></B></I>\r\n<P>We would like to thank all the sponsors who helped out and financially supported the Fall Classic. The weather held out for one more day and we thanked God for that! Everyone had a wonderful time and the only casualties from the outing were one window and a post along the cart path. I have to thank all the volunteers who woke up early Saturday morning and were willing to help set up and man holes for the contests. Weaver Ridge provided a wonderful lunch and the course was breath taking. I want to thank Patrick Hauer for being our chair person for this event, he did a great job. </P>\r\n<P>We are considering moving the golf date to late spring or early summer 2004. If you any ideas or wish to participate in the planning of next years event please contact the Advancement Office. You can call 309-686-4500 Ext: 33 or email jkammerer@peoriachristian.org.</P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>', 0, -3, 0);
