e="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">is awarded to the graduate who ranks highest (respectively) in scholarship as based on all grades for all subjects taken during the four senior high years.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The valedictorian will be recognized at graduation by wearing different color cords from the rest of the honor graduates. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Salutatorian</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">  This is awarded to the graduate who ranks second highest in their cumulative GPA for all subjects taken during their four senior high years.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The salutatorian will be recognized at graduation by the wearing different color cords form the rest of the honor graduates.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Honor Graduates- </SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Seniors completing their four high school years with an overall GPA of 85.0 and above will recognized at graduation by the wearing of gold cords.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Timothian Award</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"> - Our highest award, the Timothian Award, is given to one (1) male and one (1) female graduating senior who best exemplify the Scriptural exhortation of I Timothy 4:12 throughout his/her years at PCS as determined by their peers and the entire faculty.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>National Honor Society</FONT></H1>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial>The local chapter of the National Honor Society establishes rules for membership that are based upon a students outstanding performance in the areas of scholarship, service, leadership, and character.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>These four criteria for selection form the foundation upon which the organization and its activities are built.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Once selected, members have the responsibility to continue to demonstrate these qualities.</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l16 level1 lfo44"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Scholarship:</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Students who have a cumulative grade point average of at least 86.0 to meet the scholarship requirement for membership.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l16 level1 lfo44"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Service:</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>This quality is defined through the voluntary contributions made by a student to the school or community, done without compensation and with a positive, courteous, and enthusiastic spirit.<SPAN style="mso-tab-count: 2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">-Continued-<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">NHS Continued<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l16 level1 lfo44"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Leadership:</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Student leaders are those who are resourceful, good problem solvers, promoters of school activities, idea-contributors, dependable, and persons who exemplify positive attitudes about life.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Leadership experiences can be drawn from school, church, or community activity while working with or for others.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l16 level1 lfo44"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Christian Character:</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"> The student of good character upholds principles of morality and ethics, is cooperative, demonstrates high standards of honesty and reliability, shows courtesy, concern and respect for others. <SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN>Membership in the Peoria Christian School Chapter reflects a lifestyle that illustrates a personal commitment to Jesus Christ as Lord and Savior.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Selection procedures are as follows:<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l47 level1 lfo45"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">1.<SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Students complete the application and turn it in to the high school office by the announced deadline.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Students must have been in attendance at PCS for at least one semester to be considered.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l47 level1 lfo45"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">2.<SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Faculty will complete a character reference form for each eligible student<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l47 level1 lfo45"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">3.<SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">A five-member Faculty Council will, after reviewing all applications and reference forms, select new honorees.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l47 level1 lfo45"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">4.<SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Honorees will be announced and invited to an induction ceremony.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l47 level1 lfo45"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">5.<SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">A formal induction ceremony will be held to honor new National Honor Society members in the presence of family and friends.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Course Changes</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Pre-registration schedules for following year will be passed out during the first week of May.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Any discrepancies or changes are to be made by May 23<SUP>rd</SUP>.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Any changes made after this point will cost $10.00 to process.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Textbooks and class supplies must be ordered based on the class lists at this time.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Should a class be dropped it will be recorded as withdrawn/failing or withdrawn/passing on the transcript. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">In full year courses both semesters will be averaged together for a final course grade.</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Credit will be based on the final course grade.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Only full credit will be given.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>A failed semester may be pulled up with an improved second semester.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN><U>Partial credit will not be given for just one semester that is passed</U>.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Failing a full year course will necessitate retaking the full course in summer school or retaking it the following year in school provided there is room in that class.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Students are to work with parents to take seriously the classes for which they initially register.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Student Records</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Per the Illinois Student Records Act (Public Act 79-1108), parents and students have the right to inspect and copy the students academic and health records.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Requests should be made to the principal.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoFooter style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; tab-stops: .5in"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'"><FONT size=3>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Course Failure</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">If a high school student fails a required course for graduation, the course must be repeated, taken in summer school, or through the Illinois Virtual High School.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoFooter style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; tab-stops: .5in"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'"><FONT size=3>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Repeating Courses for Credit<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial>When a student is repeating a course, the grade from the second course will replace the previous grade from the first course, even though the new grade may be lower.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>This sometimes may result in loss of credit, (example: first time the course was taken a D was received, second time the course was taken an F was received.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The F will replace the D).</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B><FONT face=Arial>GUIDANCE AND COUNSELING SERVICES<o:p></o:p></FONT></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial>Guidance Counselors are available throughout most of the school day.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Students should sign up in the office if they desire to see a counselor.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The counselors are here to help remove any barriers from you having a successful year spiritually, academically, socially, etc.</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes"><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;</FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">ADVISOR/ADVISEE PROGRAM<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Each student will have a Faculty Advisor<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Purpose:<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">To foster the building of teacher-student rapport<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">To provide a definite program of personal contact with each student.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Each will have a faculty member available to listen to their concerns.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">To provide a teacher who may help monitor a student placed on probation from an understanding viewpoint.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">To allow for possible follow-up to events such as Life Change Week.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">The students Homeroom Teacher will be their Advisor.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><STRONG><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><STRONG><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><STRONG><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><STRONG><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><STRONG><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><STRONG><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><STRONG><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><STRONG><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><STRONG><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">EXAM EXEMPTIONS</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></STRONG></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">The exam exemption policy was developed as a reward for outstanding attendance and academic excellence.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>In the second semester, seniors may exempt final exams in any class in which they meet the following requirements:</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in; mso-list: l23 level1 lfo59"><SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><FONT face=Arial>1.</FONT><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><FONT face=Arial>A student must have a 90% average or above for the second semester in the class.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .5in; mso-list: l23 level1 lfo59"><SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><FONT face=Arial>2.</FONT><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><FONT face=Arial>A student must have no more than three (3) excused (including college visits) absences and no unexcused absences for the same period in that class for the second semester.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><FONT face=Arial>We understand that there are personal circumstances that may arise which cause a student to exceed the allowed number of absences.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>It is the students responsibility to understand that this policy was established as a reward not as a right.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText3 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><FONT face=Arial>Students in grades 9-11 are required to take exams in each of their classes.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">HOMEWORK</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Each student will have varying amounts of work to complete outside of school hours.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>This may be unfinished class work, extra projects, or memory work.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Parents should regularly check their students progress by asking to see homework papers, projects, etc.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">While parents should assist by ensuring that homework is completed and by explaining work when necessary, the work must be done by the student, and he/she must take the responsibility for it.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Parents can help their child in his/her homework by helping him/her establish good study habits.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">No homework will be given:<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l64 level1 lfo51"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">On Wednesdays (Prayer meeting night)  (Teachers will not give a test or make an assignment due on Thursdays except during exam weeks or other unique situations.)<B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><o:p></o:p></B></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l14 level1 lfo50"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Over extended holiday vacations.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Teachers will not give a test or make an assignment due on Thursdays.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The principal may make exceptions on shortened weeks.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>Homework Requests</FONT></H1>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><FONT face=Arial>When it is determined that it will be necessary to be absent for two or more days, arrangements can be made to collect homework assignments by contacting the Office before 10:00 a.m.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Homework collected by the Office will be available after 3:30 p.m. that school day.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Students are expected to complete assignments before returning to school.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold"><FONT size=2><FONT face=Arial>Cheating<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></H1>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Students are allowed to get help on most homework.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Having a problem explained to them or having something demonstrated so they can get the concept is permissible.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Copying another students paper or copying from Cliff Notes or the Internet is not allowed.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">The standard for work at PCS is that whenever a student signs his/her name to the paper they imply that all the work is their own and<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>so deserves full credit.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">MAKE-UP ASSIGNMENTS<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">When students are absent, it is the students responsibility to make up the work missed.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The student will be given a reasonable amount of time to make up the work he missed which should not exceed twice the number of days missed for up to three days.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Any absence longer than three days make-up work must be arranged with the teacher.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Work turned in within the time limit set by the teacher will be graded at full <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">credit.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Work assigned prior to an absence should be submitted <U>upon return</U>, and <U>assigned tests</U> should also be taken <U>upon return</U>.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN><U>If this is impossible due to your circumstances, please send a note with your student explaining your reasons.<o:p></o:p></U></SPAN></P>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=2><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></H1>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>FIELD TRIPS</FONT></H1>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">From time to time, the various classes take trips to interesting and educational places in the area as a vital part of the instructional program.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Parents will be notified of trips beforehand.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Fees may be charged to cover expenses.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Each field trip will have an appropriate dress code.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Students are <U>expected to attend</U> and participate in field trips.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Students are expected to show respect to tour guides and chaperones.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Misbehavior will mean an appropriate form of discipline and loss of privilege to attend future field trips.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">STUDY HALLS</SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Study hall periods are for the purpose of providing students with extra time for completing classroom work and/or assignments.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>An atmosphere of quiet is required in order for this to be accomplished.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Therefore, the following rules apply:<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l43 level1 lfo23"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Students are to be on time to study hall as in other classes.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l45 level1 lfo26"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Generally students are to study independently and without talking.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l54 level1 lfo24"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Students are to bring enough work in order to remain busy for the entire study hall period.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>No playing of games.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l9 level1 lfo21"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">When necessary for a student to leave study hall, the pass section in the students agenda must be filled out by the study hall teacher.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Students coming to study hall without an agenda may not leave class.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">-Continued-<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Study Halls Continued<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l9 level1 lfo21"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Students may use library for research or reading but are to return to Study Hall prior to the end of the period.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Students may be allowed to receive help from another student so long as their conversation stays on task and does not disturb the rest of the class.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Permission will be granted at the discretion of the study hall teacher.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; tab-stops: list .25in; mso-list: l11 level1 lfo27"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">No food or drinks are allowed in study hall.</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"> <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></H1>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold"><FONT size=2><FONT face=Arial>SUMMER READING PROGRAM<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></H1>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">All students in grades 9-12 are required to read one of the two novels listed for their grade level.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>A reading log is to be completed and signed <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">by both the student and their parents indicating that they have truly read the book.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'"><FONT size=3>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>TECHNOLOGY USE</FONT></H1>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Students and parents should secure a copy of the Acceptable Use Policy (AUP) and the AUP User Agreement Form from the IT Department or the High School Office.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold">Students are not allowed to use any computers or computer devices (PCS owned or personally owned) until they have read the Acceptable Use Policy (AUP) and have turned in an AUP User Agreement Form for the current school year.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">The Agreement Form must be signed by both the student and his/her parent/guardian.<o:p></o:p></B></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'"><FONT size=3>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'"><FONT size=3>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'"><FONT size=3>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Time