BORDER-LEFT: windowtext 1pt solid; WIDTH: 1.7in; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 1pt solid; BACKGROUND-COLOR: transparent; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt" vAlign=top width=163>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">5th oldest student <o:p></o:p></FONT></P></TD>\r\n<TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: windowtext 1pt solid; PADDING-RIGHT: 5.4pt; BORDER-TOP: #d4d0c8; PADDING-LEFT: 5.4pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; BORDER-LEFT: #d4d0c8; WIDTH: 135pt; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 1pt solid; BACKGROUND-COLOR: transparent; mso-border-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-left-alt: solid windowtext .5pt; mso-border-top-alt: solid windowtext .5pt" vAlign=top width=180>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">tuition free<o:p></o:p></FONT></P></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3><STRONG><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">Building Fee for 2003-2004<o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=3>The building fee is $480 per family each year. This fee is separate from tuition since it is paid per family rather than per student. Families with students in only PK3 (5day), PK4, or half-day kindergarten will pay only $240.00 per year for their building fee. Families with students in only PK3 (2day or 3 day) do not pay a building fee. This fee may be paid annually, or in 12 monthly payments.</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3><o:p></o:p></FONT><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">&nbsp;</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=3><STRONG>Registration Fees</STRONG></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=3>There are miscellaneous fees for class parties or retreats, assignment notebooks, student parking permits, elementary milk, yearbook, etc. These fees will be listed for specific grades in the registration packet which is available in August. Registration forms must be filled out and fees paid on Registration days. Students may not attend class until registration forms and fees are turned in.</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3><o:p></o:p></FONT><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">&nbsp;</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3><STRONG><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">Extended Care Fees for 2003-2004<o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=3>The Extended Care program is available for those families desiring a full-day program for students enrolled in the morning Pre-Kindergarten classes. Students in half-day Kindergarten will be allowed to use this service on an occasional basis. Students will be dismissed from Extended Care at <?xml:namespace prefix = st1 ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags" /><st1:time Minute="15" Hour="15">3:15 PM.</st1:time> Annual cost for this program is $900 for five afternoons per week, $540 for three afternoons per week or $6 per day.</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3><o:p></o:p></FONT><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">&nbsp;</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3><STRONG><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">After School Care<o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=3>After school care is provided by Rogy Day Care using our facilities at our California Campus. Contact <st1:City><st1:place>Sandy</st1:place></st1:City> (685-9155) directly at Rogy Day Care for times and fees.</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3><o:p></o:p></FONT><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">&nbsp;<IMG alt="" hspace=0 src="http://peoriachristian.org/uploads/0252_0__1069708233_pig.JPG" align=left border=0></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3><STRONG><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">Financial Aid<o:p></o:p></FONT></STRONG></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif"><st1:place><st1:PlaceName>Peoria</st1:PlaceName> <st1:PlaceName>Christian</st1:PlaceName> <st1:PlaceName>School</st1:PlaceName></st1:place> has set aside a certain percentage of its budget to help those families for whom tuition comes as a real burden to the familys finances. This tuition assistance is a need-based program.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=3>Our financial assistance process begins with a familys application for enrollment to the school. Upon completion and submittal of the enrollment application and application fee, a family may request a financial assistance application form from the Business Office. These applications are available in the business office in March. Much of the information needed will come from your previous years income tax return. The completed financial assistance application along with the $16.00 financial aid application fee should be mailed directly to Private School Aid Service (PSAS).<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN><STRONG>The deadline for filing your financial assistance application is April 20th.</STRONG> If you are a new family enrolling late and the April 20th deadline is past, you may still submit your financial assistance application. A small percentage of the overall budgeted amount for financial assistance is held for families enrolling after the deadline.</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3><o:p></o:p></FONT><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">&nbsp;</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=3>During the first week of June, PSA will send the school an analysis of all financial aid requests with corresponding specific information regarding each family. The Finance Committee will then review these requests and make final financial assistance determinations. You will be notified regarding the amount of assistance granted within a few days of that meeting.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>If we do not hear from you, a tuition contract, taking into account the amount of financial assistance granted, will be sent to you by the third week of June. The first tuition payment is due July 1st.</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3></FONT><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">&nbsp;</FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=3>We want you to know that the Finance Committee, as well as the Business Office, handles each application with the utmost confidentiality. Please take note of all deadlines to insure that your request will be given proper attention.</FONT></P>\r\n<P><FONT face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"></FONT></P>', 72, -3, 0);
INSERT INTO `main_content` VALUES (262, 7, 40, 0, 'Enrollment Priorities', 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, '2003-11-24', '2010-11-11', '2004-05-31', '16', '7', '', '2003-11-24', '2003-12-11', 0, 100, '<P style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px"><B><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=4>New Families</FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px"><B><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"></SPAN></B><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=3>For new families, applications are processed and students are accepted according to the date the application is received in our office as space is available (after the current family deadlines for new sibling applications and re-enrollment). However, the administration reserves the right to accept later applications to accommodate other factors vital to the overall school needs.</FONT></SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>\r\n<P><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"></SPAN><B><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=4>Current Families Enrolling New Student</FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI><B><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"></SPAN></B><FONT size=3><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif"><?xml:namespace prefix = st1 /><st1:place><st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Current</SPAN></st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"> </SPAN><st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Peoria</SPAN></st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"> </SPAN><st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Christian</SPAN></st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"> </SPAN><st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">School</SPAN></st1:PlaceName></st1:place><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"> families have the opportunity to apply for additional students from their family before January 10<SUP>th</SUP>. If you are a current family interested in enrolling a sibling for the first time at PCS, please come by the Business office to pick up a Current Family, New Student Application Form. Return the completed form with an application fee of $30.00 for each additional student you wish to enroll. After January 10<SUP>th</SUP> space will be opened up for new families for those available spaces after assuming all current students will re-enroll.</SPAN></FONT></FONT></LI></UL>\r\n<P><FONT size=3><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"></SPAN></FONT><B><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=4>Re-enrollment of Current Students</FONT></FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI><FONT size=3><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">The re-enrollment period for current students of<FONT face="times new roman, times, serif"> </FONT></SPAN></FONT><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif"><st1:place><st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Peoria</SPAN></st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"> </SPAN><st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Christian</SPAN></st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"> </SPAN><st1:PlaceName><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">School</SPAN></st1:PlaceName></st1:place><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"> is March 1<SUP>st</SUP> - March 12<SUP>th</SUP>. During this time, current students should complete the Re-enrollment Form and return it to the office with a $100.00 tuition deposit per family. (This deposit will be deducted from the first tuition payment in July.) Following the re-enrollment period, applicants will be prioritized according to the date the application or re-enrollment form and fee is received at PCS.</SPAN></FONT></FONT></LI></UL>\r\n<P><FONT size=3><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"></SPAN></FONT><B><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=4>Returning Students or Families</FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI><B><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"></SPAN></B><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif"><FONT size=3>If a family or student is applying to return to PCS after having been gone for more than 1 one year, they need to return </FONT><FONT size=3>an enrollment application and application fee and go through the same admissions process as a new family. They will have the same enrollment priority status as a new family</FONT></FONT></SPAN> </FONT>\r\n<LI><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"></SPAN><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif" size=3>If a student or family is applying to return after being away from PCS 1 year or less, testing or an interview with the principal will be required as deemed necessary. The family should return a re-enrollment form accompanied by the re-enrollment fee. Following the re-enrollment period, March 1<SUP>st</SUP>-12<SUP>th</SUP>, applicants will be prioritized according to the date the re-enrollment form and fee is received.</FONT></LI></UL>\r\n<P><FONT face="times new roman, times, serif">&nbsp;</FONT></P>', 73, 2, 0);
INSERT INTO `main_content` VALUES (263, 7, 30, 0, 'Admissions Policies', 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, '2003-11-25', '2010-05-31', '2004-05-31', '16', '7', '', '2003-11-25', '2003-12-11', 0, 100, '<P style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><B><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">General Policies</FONT></FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">An enrollment application must completed and returned to PCS accompanied by the application fee. We accept enrollment applications for future years for Pre-Kindergarten and Kindergarten classes. New family applications for grades 1-12 will be accepted only after January 1st of the year of a familys intended fall enrollment.</FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">One custodial parent (preferably both) needs to be a born-again believer. Peoria Christian School regards its mission as supporting the Christian home and church by preparing students to lead Christ-like lives through a Biblical approach to education. It is our requirement that at least one of the custodial parents have a personal relationship with Jesus Christ as their Savior and Lord. It is not necessary for the student themselves to be a believer. Special consideration is given to the students desire to attend Peoria Christian School. We also ask that the family regularly attend a Bible-believing church. \r\n<TABLE style="WIDTH: 57px; HEIGHT: 316px" cellSpacing=1 cellPadding=2 width=57 align=right border=1>\r\n<TBODY>\r\n<TR>\r\n<TD><IMG alt="" hspace=0 src="http://www.peoriachristian.org/uploads/0252_0_Praying_1069794139_100_0419b.JPG" align=baseline border=0></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">An interview with the parents, the student, the Principal, and an Admissions Committee representative is necessary. </SPAN>We ask that, where appropriate, both mother and father attend this interview. It is desirable that students who attend Peoria Christian School come from homes that reinforce the values and beliefs taught during the school day. To this end, the interview process helps assess the parents motivation in seeking the students enrollment in PCS, as well as the students willingness to attend and adhere to the discipline policies. The interview process is designed to ascertain the likelihood that the school and family can cooperate on the faith, philosophical, and academic issues involved in the education of your children.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>These interviews are normally 20 minutes in length.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>We know that this is a relatively short amount of time to get to know you, but due to the number of applications we receive and interviews that need to be conducted, we try to make these as brief and specific as possible. Should you have questions that can be answered by the Admissions Coordinator, please feel free to call any time prior to the interview.</FONT></FONT></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">PCS does not discriminate&nbsp;on the basis of&nbsp;race, color, gender, nationality&nbsp;or ethnic origin in its admission or educational policies or its scholarship, athletic, or other school-administered programs.&nbsp;The school does, however, reserve the right to deny admission to any individual who cannot benefit by the experience based on past academic achievement or whose personal lifestyle is not in harmony with the stated philosophy and purpose of PCS.<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">The applicant and parents must communicate substantial agreement with the general purposes and policies of the school.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">All school age children in the family are encouraged, but not required to enroll. </FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>\r\n<P style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><B><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><STRONG>&nbsp;</STRONG></FONT></FONT></SPAN>Age Requirements \r\n<TABLE style="WIDTH: 58px; HEIGHT: 321px" cellSpacing=1 cellPadding=2 width=58 align=right border=1>\r\n<TBODY>\r\n<TR>\r\n<TD><IMG alt="" hspace=0 src="http://www.peoriachristian.org/uploads/0252_1_ElemJesusLovesMe_1069794139_100_0979b.JPG" align=baseline border=0></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></FONT></FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">An applicant for 3 year-old Pre-Kindergarten must be three years old on or by September 1st.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">An applicant for 4 year-old Pre-Kindergarten must be four years old on or by September 1st.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">An applicant for Kindergarten must be five years old on or by September 1st.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">An applicant for first grade must be six years old on or by September 1st.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>\r\n<P style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><B><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">Academic Requirements<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">For grades 1-8, the applicant will be scheduled for a teacher check to assess the students educational needs in relation to the anticipated grade level enrollment.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">The grade placement for all students is assumed to be in accordance with previous fully completed grade level coursework. However, should previous testing, teacher checks,&nbsp;or other school records indicate a question of placement, the principal and the family will discuss and agree on the final placement and the possible insertion of additional services according to the needs of the student.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>\r\n<P style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><B><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">Health records<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">Illinois State law requires physical examinations for each student in Pre-Kindergarten, Kindergarten, 5<SUP>th</SUP>, and 9th grades. If your child is entering PCS while not in one of the above mentioned grades, we will obtain physical examination and immunization records from your childs previous school.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">All athletes must have a sports physical on file before participating.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>\r\n<P><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><B><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">Admission Decisions</FONT></FONT></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><B><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"></SPAN></B><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">You will be notified at the new family interview or within 2 business days of the status of acceptance.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><STRONG>Acceptance&nbsp;for Admission</STRONG></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</FONT></FONT></SPAN><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">We are pleased to accept families who desire an education in a Christian environment whose students are capable of achieving in a program dedicated to academic excellence. </FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">Acceptance into PCS does not mean automatic acceptance the following year. Re-admission for the school year is given to students who:</FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>\r\n<OL>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">are performing at or above grade level,</FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"></SPAN><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">attend school regularly; and<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">who have submitted to school policy and regulations during the&nbsp;school year. (In cases of new applicants, the student will be expected to have submitted to his or her previous schools regulations and policies for&nbsp;the period immediately preceding application for entry into the school.)<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV></LI></OL>\r\n<P style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><STRONG>Probationary Admission</STRONG></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">Applicants with deficiencies in any of the specified areas may be offered probationary admittance for one semester if the principal feels the deficiencies will be corrected by the end of that time. Probationary admissions are reviewed each grading period by the principal. If the necessary corrections have not occurred, the student will be denied further admittance.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>\r\n<P style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman"><STRONG>Denial of Admission</STRONG> <o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">For academic or other reasons, this will be communicated to the family at the interview, or via mail or phone. <o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">If we do not accept a student at Peoria Christian School, the application fee will be refunded.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<LI>\r\n<DIV style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0.25in"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">Denial of admission does not prohibit a student from applying again if the deficient areas are corrected.<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>\r\n<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></P>\r\n<P>&nbsp;</P>', 74, 2, 0);
INSERT INTO `main_content` VALUES (264, 5, 5, 0, 'Pre-Kindergarten 4', 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, 0, '0000-00-00', 1, '2003-10-15', '2005-05-31', '2005-05-31', '99999', '18', 'Pre-Kindergarten', '2003-10-23', '2004-08-19', 4, 100, '<P class=MsoTitle style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 14pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><STRONG>\r\n<CENTER>Pre-Kindergarten 4</CENTER>\r\n<CENTER>&nbsp;</STRONG></SPAN></CENTER>\r\n<CENTER><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3><EM>Train up a child in the way he should go, and when he is old he will not depart from it.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Proverbs 22:6<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></EM></FONT></SPAN></CENTER>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><o:p><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>Our Purpose<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></H1>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><o:p><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>The Peoria Christian School Pre-Kindergarten program supports the Christian home and church by preparing students to lead Christ-like lives through a biblical approach to education.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>We accomplish this through a variety of methods that are age-appropriate.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Children are given opportunities to form a solid foundation academically in reading and math readiness, as well as acquire fine and gross motor skills.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Character development and spiritual growth are important goals of our Pre-Kindergarten program.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><o:p><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>Our Staff<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></H1>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><o:p><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>The teachers in our program maintain a personal relationship with Jesus Christ.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>We guide and direct the children out of a prayerful heart of love and concern.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Our certified teachers plan fun, age-appropriate activities to help the children have a positive experience at school.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><o:p><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>Our Curriculum<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></H1>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><o:p><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>Our Pre-Kindergarten 4 uses the Association of Christian Schools International (ACSI) curriculum for Bible and reading.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Children have a Bible story and a Bible verse each week.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>They learn to identify the alphabet as well as being introduced to the sounds of the letters.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>They learn to identify numerals 1  20, count objects using one-to-one correspondence, and identify shapes.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>The teachers use biblical integration throughout the day.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><o:p><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>Our Activities<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></H1>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><o:p><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>Children participate in a variety of activities during the day, such as calendar, pledges, singing, and group time instruction about topics for the day.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>They will practice and strengthen their fine motor skills through coloring, cutting, gluing, painting, puzzles, water and sand table activities, and manipulative games.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Our playground will delight them as their gross motor skills develop.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Children also grow socially and emotionally by practicing good manners, sharing toys, helping in the classroom, and obeying the teacher.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Their work habits form as they participate in many learning experiences including housekeeping, blocks, games, art, math, science, and books.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>They will be involved in music, physical education, and library each week, also.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Field trips are scheduled throughout the year to complement the learning in the classroom.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><o:p><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></P>\r\n<H1 style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left" align=left><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>Our Requirements and Schedule<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></H1>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center><B><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><o:p><FONT size=3>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.75in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .75in"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"><FONT size=3></FONT><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>Children need to be four years old by September 1<SUP>st</SUP>.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.75in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .75in"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"><FONT size=3></FONT><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT size=3><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Class size is limited to a staff-to-student ratio of </SPAN><?xml:namespace prefix = st1 ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:smarttags" /><st1:time Minute="15" Hour="13"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial">1:15</SPAN></st1:time><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial">. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.75in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .75in"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"><FONT size=3></FONT><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>Our program requires the children to be completely toilet trained prior to the first day of school. <o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.75in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .75in"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"><FONT size=3></FONT><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT size=3><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Each child needs a physical examination less than six-months old to begin in our program as required by the state of </SPAN><st1:State><st1:place><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Illinois</SPAN></st1:place></st1:State><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial">.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN><o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.75in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .75in"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"><FONT size=3></FONT><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><FONT size=3>A five-day option is available, as well as a three-day option of<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday.<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\r\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.75in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .75in"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"><FONT size=3></FONT><SPAN style="FONT: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT size=3><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Class times are </SPAN><st1:time Minute="30" Hour="8"><SPAN style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial">8:30 a.m.</SPAN>